u AlwaAqiEu", "text_ar": "النَّسْرُ الوَاقِعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Falling,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Alighting, Vulture,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~asoru AlT~aAy^iru", "text_ar": "النَّسْرُ الطَّايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Flying Vulture,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two stars"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "asterisms,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * M, A, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well-known,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which together are called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~asoraAni", "text_ar": "النَّسْرَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Two Vultures"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (M, A,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and each of which alone is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~asoru", "text_ar": "النَّسْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nasorN", "text_ar": "نَسْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "being likened to the bird so named:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the former is the bright star"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[a]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the constellation"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~aloyaAqu", "text_ar": "الشَّلْيَاقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Lyra"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "likened by the Arabs to a vulture"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nsr", "text_ar": "نسر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that has contracted its wings to itself, as though it had alighted upon something:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the latter consists of the three well-known stars"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[a"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "b"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "g]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the constellation"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEuqaAbu", "text_ar": "العُقَابُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Aquila"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Kzw:) [The former rose heliacally, about the epoch of the Flight, in central Arabia, on the 25th of November, O. S., with the Eighteenth Mansion of the Moon, which is a of Scorpio; and the latter, on the 28th of December, O. S.: and both set, together, anti-heliacally, at that period and in that part, on the 24th of July, O. S. See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nawo'N", "text_ar": "نَوْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dabuwrN", "text_ar": "دَبُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nasorN", "text_ar": "نَسْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~asoru", "text_ar": "النَّسْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, K,) the latter occurring in a verse cited in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ez", "text_ar": "عز"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain idol,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "belonging to Dhu-l-Kelaa,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the land of Himyer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaguwvu", "text_ar": "يَغُوثُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "did to Medhhij, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaEuwqu", "text_ar": "يَعُوقُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "t